## 10. 📊 Code Coverage e Relatórios

### 10.1. Configuração de Coverage

```xml
<!-- Directory.Build.props ou .csproj -->
<PropertyGroup>
    <CollectCoverage>true</CollectCoverage>
    <CoverletOutputFormat>opencover</CoverletOutputFormat>
    <CoverletOutput>./coverage/</CoverletOutput>
    <Exclude>[*.Tests]*,[*.TestHelpers]*</Exclude>
    <ExcludeByAttribute>GeneratedCodeAttribute,ExcludeFromCodeCoverageAttribute</ExcludeFromCodeCoverageAttribute>
</PropertyGroup>
```

### 10.2. Comandos

```bash
# Executar testes com coverage
dotnet test /p:CollectCoverage=true /p:CoverletOutputFormat=opencover

# Coverage com relatório HTML (usando ReportGenerator)
dotnet test /p:CollectCoverage=true /p:CoverletOutputFormat=cobertura
reportgenerator -reports:coverage.cobertura.xml -targetdir:coveragereport -reporttypes:Html

# Coverage com threshold
dotnet test /p:CollectCoverage=true /p:Threshold=80 /p:ThresholdType=line
```

### 10.3. Atributos para Exclusão

```csharp
// ✅ CORRETO - Excluir código gerado de coverage
[ExcludeFromCodeCoverage]
public class GeneratedClass
{
    // Código gerado automaticamente
}

// ✅ CORRETO - Excluir propriedades triviais
public class User
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    
    [ExcludeFromCodeCoverage]
    public string FullName => $"{FirstName} {LastName}";
}
```

